paragraphs.text: as the winter winds litter london with lonely hearts. oh the warmth in your eyes swept me into your arms. was it love or fear of the cold that led us through the night? for every kiss your beauty trumped my doubt.
and my head told my heart "let love grow.". but my heart told my head

"this time no, this time no!". we'll be washed and buried one day my girl. and the time we were given will be left for the world. the flesh that lived and loved will be eaten by plague. so let the memories be good for those who stay.
